00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:31.430
historical-median-male-heightThings began
to change after WWII.

00:03:31.430 --> 00:03:35.410
In the last half century or so, the average
American height has more or less remained

00:03:35.410 --> 00:03:39.959
the same, while post-war Europeans have, on
the whole, sprouted like crazy.

00:03:39.959 --> 00:03:44.690
In the most extreme case, throughout the 19th
century men and women of the Netherlands averaged

00:03:44.690 --> 00:03:54.490
roughly 5’5″ (166 cm) for men and 5’1″
(156 cm) for women- relatively short for their

00:03:54.490 --> 00:03:56.239
era and region of the world.

00:03:56.239 --> 00:04:00.239
Today, the tallest people in the world are
found in the Netherlands, where the average

00:04:00.239 --> 00:04:06.670
man is just over 6 feet tall (183 cm) and
the average woman is nearly 5’7″ (170

00:04:06.670 --> 00:04:07.670
cm).

00:04:07.670 --> 00:04:16.760
By comparison, American men are 5’9″ (175
cm) on average, and women are 5’4″ (163

00:04:16.760 --> 00:04:17.940
cm).

00:04:17.940 --> 00:04:22.780
Some believe that the great strides in height
made by Western Europeans over Americans can

00:04:22.780 --> 00:04:28.070
be attributed to their universal health coverage
and other social policies, such as maternity

00:04:28.070 --> 00:04:33.780
services and greater parental leave allowing
for better practicality of things like breastfeeding

00:04:33.780 --> 00:04:38.690
vs. formula fed and, later, more time off
work providing extra time for preparing nutritious

00:04:38.690 --> 00:04:43.700
meals, rather than relying on fast-food and
other quick high-calorie, low nutrition “junk”

00:04:43.700 --> 00:04:44.700
foods.

00:04:44.700 --> 00:04:48.150
Further, the so-called “over-nutrition”
prevalent in the U.S., combined with lack

00:04:48.150 --> 00:04:52.690
of physical activity leading to widespread
obesity, has also been noted for its negative

00:04:52.690 --> 00:04:58.169
effects on growth hormones and metabolism,
limiting the ultimate adult height somewhat.

00:04:58.169 --> 00:05:01.610
So how high will humans grow with perfect
nutrition and health care?

00:05:01.610 --> 00:05:06.040
It’s generally thought the Dutch are close
to the peak of average human height potential,

00:05:06.040 --> 00:05:11.280
at least based on innate genetics, and Americans
and others are close to it.

00:05:11.280 --> 00:05:15.530
This is probably a good thing as the human
body is not adapted well for extreme height,

00:05:15.530 --> 00:05:20.940
and those outliers who do tower over the rest
of us often suffer from various pains and

00:05:20.940 --> 00:05:36.550
other debilities related to their abnormal
height as they age.

